article.headline: Rice 78, Idaho State 62
article.story: FAIRBANKS, Alaska (AP) -- Jeff Gardner scored 22 points to lead Idaho State to a 78-62 victory over Binghamton in a consolation round game Saturday at the BP Top of the World Classic. Gardner shot 5-for-7 from 3-point range and the Bengals (1-1) converted 11 of 21 shots from beyond the arc. Center Nick Billings led Binghamton with 15 points, six rebounds and three blocked shots. Scott Henry had 13 points and five rebounds for Idaho State. There were six ties and five lead changes in the first half before Idaho State went on a 10-3 run and extended its lead to 30-23, with 5:04 remaining. Gardner had 12 first-half points, and the Bengals led 41-35 at the break. A 20-5 run early in the second half gave Idaho State its biggest lead at 61-43, with 10:39 remaining. Binghamton (0-2) went on a 16-2 and closed within four points when Billy Williams hit a pair of free throws with 5:58 remaining. But the Bearcats went nearly the entire final eight minutes without a field goal until Troy Halley made a layup with 12 seconds remaining. Binghamton was slowed by poor free-throw shooting finishing 13-for-24 in the game.
